{"id":"5837","name":"Colour Picker","tagline":"Easily generate a solid colour image!","icon":"ios14 c2846468607 g59771","latest":"25611","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<h1>Description</h1>\n<p>Colour picker is a Shortcut that allows you to pick any colour and gives an output of that colour as an image. </p>\n<p>Colours can be chosen in many ways, including:<br>\n</p><ul>\n <li>RGB</li>\n <li>Hex Code</li>\n <li>Random Colour</li>\n <li>Colour names (140+ choices)</li>\n <li>Standard colours (17 choices)</li>\n</ul><p></p>\n<p>The final result is a solid image of the chosen colour and is a 720x720px square.  </p>\n<p>This Shortcut can also be used as a Snippet/Shortcut within a Shortcut to easily generate a colour when needed.  </p>\n<h1>For developers</h1>\n<p>For other Shortcut developers who want to implement this Shortcut inside another Shortcut, add any Shortcut input of any type in the ‘Run Shortcut’ action. This will give an output of the colour image without bringing a menu asking to save the colour.</p>\n<h1>Gallery</h1>\n<p><img alt=\"Image1\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/y26thtt.jpg\"></p>\n<p><img alt=\"Image2\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/sMUiYKr.jpg\"></p>\n<p><img alt=\"Image3\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/viZSEgU.jpg\"></p>\n<p><img alt=\"Image4\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/BfFgvgj.jpg\"></p>\n<p><img alt=\"Image5\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/c1jetkn.jpg\"></p>\n\t\t\t\t","releasenotes":"<p><strong>1.10 - Feb. 24, 2021, 7:44 p.m.</strong></p><p>Minor improvements</p>"}